@NODE Introduction "Introduction to Pumpkin"

 @{b}About@{ub}

  Pumpkin is copyright © 1996 Martin Wulffeld. All Rights Reserved.

  It uses the ReqTools library which is copyright © Nico François.

  Pumpkin requires at least Kickstart 3.0.

 @{b}What it does@{ub}

  Pumpkin is a C function and structure lister for CygnusEd. You might
  already have an idea of what such a lister does. When activated Pumpkin
  scans the current active file in CygnusEd and finds the C functions and
  C structures that were possible to find. Thereafter, it opens a window
  on the screen CygnusEd with a list of the functions and structures found.
  From this window you can via the keyboard fast and easily jump between
  the functions and structures in your source.
@ENDNODE

